Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic increasingly visit the official website of the Office of the Federal Service of bailiffs of Russia on Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself, more than 42 thousand - the section "Bank of data of executive proceedings", 661 payment receipts on payment of debts were downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council under the Federal Federal Tax Service of Russia, almost every resident of the region is charged with debts for utility payments, traffic fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is immune from unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the FSFSP of Russia for Kazakhstan recommends everyone who has planned a trip abroad, to clarify in the department of bailiffs at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information on the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The Service has created a “Bank of Data Executive Proceedings” for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional sites of the FSFSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communication devices iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The database contains information about the enforcement proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains Delgir Bodgayev, assistant head of the FSFSP of Russia for Kazakhstan.
"In the presence of debts, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the enforcement letter or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the bailiff's department; the name of the bailiff-executor; contact phone number.
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
