The Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation predicted the rate of the ruble for 17 years
The Russian Ministry of Finance expects a gradual weakening of the ruble exchange rate - up to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast, submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the ruble rate, according to the forecast, will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the next five years - 73.9.
The Office notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective rate (an indicator that takes into account the changes in the exchange rates of the countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As for inflation, by 2020 it will be 3.5%, and then stabilize at the level of about 4%, according to the Ministry of Finance.
